  "tips": [
    "Really nice small town that has plenty of resupply options and some hotels to sleep in.",
    "Nice track to climb to the Portillon in Gravel/MTB mode. The part that goes over the pass remains quite flat for a while before actually starting the descent to Bossost. So, it's a nice spot to come and ride in the quiet mountains in family mode with children who are new to mountain biking, for example.",
    "The Col du Portillón is a short but intense mountain pass that connects the Aran Valley to France via a narrow, shady road through forests. Its ascent, with its pleasant slopes, is highly appreciated by local and professional cyclists.",
    "Located at an altitude of 1,750 meters on the border with France, it offers wonderful views, to the north, of the spectacular Maladetas massif (3,312 m)."
  ],
